frus:attachment.p:
On the analysis of iridized platinum, used by the French section of the
                            International Metric Commission in the manufacture of prototypes, by
                            Messrs. H. Sainte-Claire Deville and J. S. Stas;

Specific weights and coefficients of diction of platinum and of the
                            metals which accompany it, as likewise the alloys of these metals, by O.
                            O. J. Broch;

List of the deductions to be made
                                    from the sum of 64,560 francs,
                                    constituting the last payment according to article 6 of the old contract.

As to the scales the bureau has already received the largest of these
                                for the transposition of weights, by Mr. Ruprecht; the three others,
                                by the same constructor, will be delivered soon.

Finally, the bureau received, in the month of July, Mr. Laurent’s
                                apparatus for measuring dilation according to the Fizcau system;
                                this appaiatus is now undergoing an examination.
